		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=754&amp;sid=2d2e0553aca2921974122d55b518fd52" style="color: #00AA00;" class="username-coloured">dom</a></strong> &raquo; Tue Jul 24, 2012 6:04 pm </div>

			

			<div class="content">I've had a think about this and it's something that the GPU can do almost for free.<br /><br />Try this build:<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://dl.dropbox.com/u/3669512/temp/start_rot.elf">https://dl.dropbox.com/u/3669512/temp/start_rot.elf</a><!-- m --><br /><br />and add<br />display_rotate=1<br />to config.txt.<br /><br />(1=90, 2=180, 3=270 degrees of rotation)<br /><br />There's definitely some issues with this build, like fbset, and how hdmi resolutions are reported (should they be 1920x1080 or 1080x1920?).<br /><br />But give it a go.</div>

			

		</div>

		
